properties.name: key
properties.description: • key - (Required) The project's unique key.

properties.name: name
properties.description: • name - (Required) The project's name.

properties.name: tags
properties.description: • tags - (Optional) The project's set of tags.

properties.name: project_key
properties.description: • project_key - (Required) - The environment's project key.

properties.name: name
properties.description: • name - (Required) The name of the environment.

properties.name: key
properties.description: • key - (Required) The project-unique key for the environment.

properties.name: color
properties.description: • color - (Required) The color swatch as an RGB hex value with no leading #. For example: 000000.

properties.name: secure_mode
properties.description: • secure_mode - (Optional) Set to true to ensure a user of the client-side SDK cannot impersonate another user.

properties.name: default_track_events
properties.description: • default_track_events - (Optional) Set to true to enable data export for every flag created in this environment after you configure this argument. To learn more, read Data Export.

properties.name: default_ttl
properties.description: • default_ttl - (Optional) The TTL for the environment. This must be between 0 and 60 minutes. The TTL setting only applies to environments using the PHP SDK. To learn more, read TTL settings.

properties.name: project_key
properties.description: • project_key - (Required) The feature flag's project key.

properties.name: key
properties.description: • key - (Required) The unique feature flag key that references the flag in your application code.

properties.name: name
properties.description: • name - (Required) The human-readable name of the feature flag.

properties.name: variation_type
properties.description: • variation_type - (Required) The feature flag's variation type: boolean, string, number or json.

properties.name: variations
properties.description: • variations - (Required) List of nested blocks describing the variations associated with the feature flag. You must specify at least two variations. To learn more, read Nested Variations Blocks.

properties.name: description
properties.description: • description - (Optional) The feature flag's description.

properties.name: tags
properties.description: • tags - (Optional) Set of feature flag tags.

properties.name: maintainer_id
properties.description: • maintainer_id - (Optional) The feature flag maintainer's team member ID.

properties.name: temporary
properties.description: • temporary - (Optional) Specifies whether the flag is a temporary flag.

properties.name: include_in_snippet
properties.description: • include_in_snippet - (Optional) Specifies whether this flag should be made available to the client-side JavaScript SDK.

properties.name: custom_properties
properties.description: • custom_properties - (Optional) List of nested blocks describing the feature flag's custom properties. To learn more, read Nested Custom Properties.

properties.name: nested-variations-blocks
properties.description: » Nested Variations Blocks
Nested variations blocks have the following structure:

properties.name: value
properties.description: • value - (Required) The variation value. The value's type must correspond to the variation_type argument. For example: variation_type = "boolean" accepts only true or false.

properties.name: name
properties.description: • name - (Optional) The name of the variation.

properties.name: description
properties.description: • description - (Optional) The variation's description.

properties.name: nested-custom-properties
properties.description: » Nested Custom Properties
Nested custom_properties have the following structure:

properties.name: key
properties.description: • key - (Required) The unique custom property key.

properties.name: name
properties.description: • name - (Required) The name of the custom property.

properties.name: value
properties.description: • value - (Required) The list of custom property value strings.

properties.name: flag_id
properties.description: • flag_id - (Required) The feature flag's unique id in the format project_key/flag_key.

properties.name: env_key
properties.description: • env_key - (Required) The environment key.

properties.name: targeting_enabled
properties.description: • targeting_enabled - (Optional) Whether targeting is enabled.

properties.name: track_events
properties.description: • track_events - (Optional) Whether to send event data back to LaunchDarkly.

properties.name: off_variation
properties.description: • off_variation - (Optional) The index of the variation to serve if targeting is disabled.

properties.name: prerequisites
properties.description: • prerequisites - (Optional) List of nested blocks describing prerequisite feature flags rules. To learn more, read Nested Prequisites Blocks.

properties.name: user_targets
properties.description: • user_targets - (Optional) List of nested blocks describing the individual user targets for each variation. The order of the user_targets blocks determines the index of the variation to serve if a user_target is matched. To learn more, read Nested User Target Blocks.

properties.name: rules
properties.description: • rules - (Optional) List of logical targeting rules. To learn more, read Nested Rules Blocks.

properties.name: flag_fallthrough
properties.description: • flag_fallthrough - (Optional) Nested block describing the default variation to serve if no prerequisites, user_target, or rules apply. To learn more, read Nested Flag Fallthrough Block.

properties.name: nested-prerequisites-blocks
properties.description: » Nested Prerequisites Blocks
Nested prerequisites blocks have the following structure:

properties.name: flag_key
properties.description: • flag_key - (Required) The prerequisite feature flag's key.

properties.name: variation
properties.description: • variation - (Required) The index of the prerequisite feature flag's variation to target.

properties.name: nested-user-targets-blocks
properties.description: » Nested User Targets Blocks
Nested user_targets blocks have the following structure:

properties.name: values
properties.description: (Optional) List of user strings to target.

properties.name: nested-flag-fallthrough-block
properties.description: » Nested Flag Fallthrough Block
The nested flag_fallthrough block has the following structure:

properties.name: variation
properties.description: • variation - (Optional) The default integer variation index to serve if no prerequisites, user_target, or rules apply. You must specify either variation or rollout_weights.

properties.name: rollout_weights
properties.description: • rollout_weights - (Optional) List of integer percentage rollout weights to apply to each variation if no prerequisites, user_target, or rules apply. The sum of the rollout_weights must equal 1000000. You must specify either variation or rollout_weights.

properties.name: nested-rules-blocks
properties.description: » Nested Rules Blocks
Nested rules blocks have the following structure:

properties.name: clauses
properties.description: • clauses - (Required) List of nested blocks specifying the logical clauses to evaluate. To learn more, read Nested Clauses Blocks.

properties.name: variation
properties.description: • variation - (Optional) The integer variation index to serve if the rule clauses evaluate to true. You must specify either variation or rollout_weights.

properties.name: rollout_weights
properties.description: • rollout_weights - (Optional) List of integer percentage rollout weights to apply to each variation if the rule clauses evaluates to true. The sum of the rollout_weights must equal 1000000. You must specify either variation or rollout_weights.

properties.name: nested-clauses-blocks
properties.description: » Nested Clauses Blocks
Nested clauses blocks have the following structure:

properties.name: attribute
properties.description: • attribute - (Required) The user attribute to operate on.

properties.name: op
properties.description: • op - (Required) The operator associated with the rule clause. Available options are in, endsWith, startsWith, matches, contains, lessThan, lessThanOrEqual, greaterThanOrEqual, before, after, segmentMatch, semVerEqual, semVerLessThan, and semVerGreaterThan.

properties.name: values
properties.description: • values - (Required) The list of values associated with the rule clause.

properties.name: negate
properties.description: • negate - (Required) Whether to negate the rule clause.
Nested flag_fallthrough blocks have the following structure:

properties.name: variation
properties.description: • variation - (Optional) The integer variation index to serve if the rule clauses evaluate to true. You must specify either variation or rollout_weights.

properties.name: rollout_weights
properties.description: • rollout_weights - (Optional) List of integer percentage rollout weights to apply to each variation if the rule clauses evaluates to true. The sum of the rollout_weights must equal 1000000. You must specify either variation or rollout_weights.

properties.name: key
properties.description: • key - (Required) The unique key that references the segment.

properties.name: project_key
properties.description: • project_key - (Required) The segment's project key.

properties.name: env_key
properties.description: • env_key - (Required) The segment's environment key.

properties.name: name
properties.description: • name - (Required) The human-friendly name for the segment.

properties.name: description
properties.description: • description - (Optional) The description of the segment's purpose.

properties.name: tags
properties.description: • tags - (Optional) Set of tags for the segment.

properties.name: included
properties.description: • included - (Optional) List of users included in the segment.

properties.name: excluded
properties.description: • excluded - (Optional) List of user excluded from the segment.

properties.name: rules
properties.description: • rules - (Optional) List of nested custom rule blocks to apply to the segment. To learn more, read Nested Rules Blocks.

properties.name: nested-rules-blocks
properties.description: » Nested Rules Blocks
Nested rules blocks have the following structure:

properties.name: weight
properties.description: • weight - (Optional) The integer weight of the rule (between 1 and 100000).

properties.name: bucket_by
properties.description: • bucket_by - (Optional) The operator used to group users together. Available options are in, endsWith, startsWith, matches, contains, lessThan, lessThanOrEqual, greaterThanOrEqual, before, after, segmentMatch, semVerEqual, semVerLessThan, and semVerGreaterThan.

properties.name: clauses
properties.description: • clauses - (Optional) List of nested custom rule clause blocks. To learn more, read Nested Clauses Blocks.

properties.name: nested-clauses-blocks
properties.description: » Nested Clauses Blocks
Nested clauses blocks have the following structure:

properties.name: attribute
properties.description: • attribute - (Required) The user attribute to operate on.

properties.name: op
properties.description: • op - (Required) The operator associated with the rule clause. Available options are in, endsWith, startsWith, matches, contains, lessThan, lessThanOrEqual, greaterThanOrEqual, before, after, segmentMatch, semVerEqual, semVerLessThan, and semVerGreaterThan.

properties.name: values
properties.description: • values - (Required) The list of values associated with the rule clause.

properties.name: negate
properties.description: • negate - (Required) Whether to negate the rule clause.

properties.name: url
properties.description: • url - (Required) - The URL of the remote webhook.

properties.name: enabled
properties.description: • enabled - (Required) - Specifies whether the webhook is enabled.

properties.name: name
properties.description: • name - (Optional) - The webhook's human-readable name.

properties.name: secret
properties.description: • secret - (Optional) - The secret used to sign the webhook.

properties.name: tags
properties.description: • tags - (Optional) - Set of tags associated with the webhook.

properties.name: key
properties.description: • key - (Required) The unique key that references the custom role.

properties.name: name
properties.description: • name - (Required) The human-readable name for the custom role.

properties.name: description
properties.description: • description - (Optional) The description of the custom role.

properties.name: policy
properties.description: • policy - (Required) The custom role policy block. To learn more, read Policies in custom roles.
Custom role policy blocks are composed of the following arguments:

properties.name: effect
properties.description: • effect - (Required) - Either allow or deny. This argument defines whether the statement allows or denies access to the named resources and actions.

properties.name: resources
properties.description: • resources - (Required) - The list of resource specifiers defining the resources to which the statement applies or does not apply.

properties.name: actions
properties.description: • actions - (Required) The list of action specifiers defining the actions to which the statement applies.

properties.name: email
properties.description: • email - (Required) The unique email address associated with the team member.

properties.name: first_name
properties.description: • first_name - (Optional) The team member's given name.

properties.name: last_name
properties.description: • last_name - (Optional) The team member's family name.

properties.name: role
properties.description: • role - (Optional) The role associated with team member. Supported roles are reader, writer, or admin. If you don't specify a role, reader is assigned by default.

properties.name: custom_role
properties.description: • custom_role - (Optional) The list of custom roles keys associated with the team member. Custom roles are only available to customers on enterprise plans. To learn more about enterprise plans, contact sales@launchdarkly.com.
Note: each launchdarkly_team_member must have either a role or custom_role argument.
